Show HN: Using GPT-3 to select holiday gifts
text:
A ton of people, myself included, have issues with figuring out what gift to buy for people. The problem is often I have no idea how to go about figuring out what to but. So I used GPT to help me select gifts.

I used this as an opportunity to explore Chat UIs, beyond the ChatGPT/messaging ones we are used to. I think that having "state" shown on the side can help enhance the UI. I'm really interested in using LLMs as reasoning agents, so trying to get a language model to reason about what gift to get is a good starting point. I'd love tips on how to make the UI better and where to go from here!

Show HN: Tunll – secure tunnels to localhost for all developers
text:
With Tunll you can easily serve local HTTP(S) and TCP apps on the public internet. Build webhooks, share in-progress work, tunnel into Docker and Kubernetes containers, access IoT devices in the field, and more.

Single binary for all OS includes both the agent and the optional self-hosted server.

$ tunll http 8080 $ tunll tcp 22
